                  </persName>
            . I am butler of Staple's-inn. Mr. Cookeny took a cellar there, and in clearing it out I found this stove, and put it into a recess in the garden, from which the prisoner took it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man, who looked like a bricklayer, told me to carry the stove to Cursitor-street, and he would give me a job.</p>
